Define a function<p><pre><code>  var ... = function( ... ){ ... };
</code></pre>
named generate<p><pre><code>  var generate = function( ... ){ ... };
</code></pre>
that takes one argument, a function f<p><pre><code>  var generate = function( f ){ ... };
</code></pre>
It should return an array<p><pre><code>  var generate = function( f ){ return [ ... ]; };
</code></pre>
that consists of the function f<p><pre><code>  var generate = function( f ){ return [ f, ... ]; };
</code></pre>
and another function<p><pre><code>  var generate = function( f ){ return [ f, function( ... ){ ... } ]; };
</code></pre>
that doubles its input<p><pre><code>  var generate = function( f ){ return [ f, function( x ){ return 2*x; } ]; };</code></pre>
